LOCUS       GENTLE_MAMMALIAN_LUCIFERASE_V1 3301 bp    DNA     circular SYN 16-APR-2026
DEFINITION  Synthetic promoterless mammalian luciferase reporter backbone
            for deterministic VKORC1/rs9923231 tutorial handoff.
ACCESSION   GENTLE_MAMMALIAN_LUCIFERASE_V1
VERSION     GENTLE_MAMMALIAN_LUCIFERASE_V1.1
KEYWORDS    synthetic construct; mammalian reporter; luciferase; tutorial.
SOURCE      synthetic DNA construct
  ORGANISM  synthetic DNA construct
            other sequences; artificial sequences.
COMMENT     Pinned local tutorial backbone for offline ClawBio->GENtle
            promoter-reporter planning. This is a synthetic, tutorial-owned
            promoterless mammalian luciferase reporter architecture chosen
            so the canonical rs9923231 demo does not depend on live GenBank
            retrieval. It is intended for deterministic construct building,
            rendering, and documentation rather than as an exact deposited
            plasmid sequence. The intended assay class is transient
            transfection in human cells.
FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     source          1..3301
                     /organism="synthetic DNA construct"
                     /mol_type="other DNA"
     misc_feature    1..160
                     /label="promoterless_insertion_site"
                     /note="Synthetic promoterless insertion site for the offline VKORC1 luciferase tutorial backbone. Insert promoter fragments upstream of luc2 for mammalian transient-transfection reporter planning."
     CDS             161..1816
                     /gene="luc2"
                     /product="luciferase 2"
                     /label="luc2"
                     /note="Synthetic luciferase reporter CDS placeholder for deterministic map rendering; backbone architecture is tutorial-focused rather than sequence-exact to a deposited plasmid."
     misc_feature    1840..1948
                     /label="SV40 polyA"
                     /note="Synthetic polyadenylation feature placeholder for mammalian reporter planning."
     CDS             complement(2020..2880)
                     /gene="bla"
